&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*********£2,500 ‘Golden Hello’ Payment**********&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Awarded with this vacancy!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now and if you are successfully recruited you will receive £2,500&lt;strong&gt;- does not apply to current HIOW NHS Staff&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5 Nurse Salary plus relocation allowance (subject to terms and conditions)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are looking for an active role to develop your clinical skills in the area of caring for older people, then we have the position for you. You will be responsible for working in partnership with the whole team and will play a vital role in the development of the ward.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our inpatient service provides intensive care, support and treatment for older people in Hampshire with acute mental health problems.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for someone who is self-motivated, enthusiastic and positive about the care of older people. You must be a highly motivated, competent and flexible practitioner. You will be part of the team assessing needs and providing an individualised plan of care for patients, and support for family and carers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You need to be able to demonstrate; strong interpersonal, communication and presentation skills, be organised and possess good IT skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return for your flexibility and commitment we can offer excellent training and personal development support to make sure you have the latest clinical knowledge. To enable you to perform at your best you will receive regular supervision; team support and dedicated help to get you through Nurse Revalidation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post would be suitable for RMN registered applicants as well as newly qualified student nurses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Basingstoke is a fast paced, vibrant and modern town surrounded by picturesque villages and set in the stunning Hampshire Countryside. Within easy reach of London the hospital is located close to excellent road and rail networks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We will be in touch with you as soon as you apply and aim for interviews to be within 7 days from date of application. Please check your email account for updates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please be advised that previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Happy to Talk Flexible Working- allrequests for flexible and part time working will be considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Follow us on Facebook and on Twitter: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;facebook.com/SouthernHealthNHS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
